1. Network Policy:
There are three pods where the applications deployed. Front-end, API Server, Database Server.

User(request) ---> Front-end ---> API-Server --> Database
Database(response)---> API-Server --> Front-end ---> User

Ingress: Incoming traffic
Step 1: User --> Front-end (ingress traffic from user)
Step 3: Front-end ---> API-Server (ingress traffic from frontend)
Step 5: API-Server --> Database (ingress traffic from apiserver)


Egress: Outgoing traffic
Step 2: Front-end ---> API-Server (egress traffic for frontend)
Step 4: API-Server --> Database (egress traffic for apiserver)


Here all the pods doesn't required to connect each due to network policy implemented.
POD A reach POD B
POD B reach POD C
POD A not reach POD C (network policy applied in the POD C where the ingress traffic should be only from POD B)

Ingress traffic:::
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: test-network-policy
  namespace: default
spec:
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      role: db
  policyTypes:
  - Ingress
  ingress:
  - from:
    - podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          role: frontend
    ports:
    - protocol: TCP
      port: 6379




Important network policy:

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: test-network-policy
  namespace: default
spec:
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      role: db
  policyTypes:
  - Ingress
  - Egress
  ingress:
  - from:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 172.17.0.0/16
        except:
        - 172.17.1.0/24
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          project: myproject
    - podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          role: frontend
    ports:
    - protocol: TCP
      port: 6379
  egress:
  - to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 10.0.0.0/24
    ports:
    - protocol: TCP
      port: 5978

Step 1: 
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      role: db
the match lables for the network policy is role:db


Step 2:
policyTypes:
  - Ingress
  - Egress

Policy type is ingress and egress

Step 3:
ingress:
  - from:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 172.17.0.0/16
        except:
        - 172.17.1.0/24
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          project: myproject
    - podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          role: frontend
    ports:
    - protocol: TCP
      port: 6379

POD B (api pod) frontend label --> POD C (database pod)

Database pod's port is 6379 and tcp protocol.

Database pod should decide the ingress traffic, based on podSelector (frontend role). Only the api pod will reach to database.

Namespace label is myproject for production, so only the api pod from the production environment will reach the database pod.

There is an database backup server which has to query from database, only the server IP 172.17.0.0/16 will reach database except -
 172.17.1.0/24


Step 4: 

egress:
  - to:
    - ipBlock:
        cidr: 10.0.0.0/24
    ports:
    - protocol: TCP
      port: 5978

Database pod will allow the outgoing traffic to the database backup server ip 10.0.0.0/24 with port 5978



Note:
If a pod allow ingress traffic from the other pods, outgoing traffic to the same pods will happen automatically. Specific policy configuration
is not required.






